records.addlTxt: CLARIFYING Sentencing hearing of 02-08-2016:  Defendant has until 02-08-2017 to pay restitution or Civil Judgment WITH Tax Intercept.  sdg

Defendant Joseph James Rodriguez in court with attorney Bridget Joy Krause.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

On motion of the state, the court amended Count 1 to:

Count 1 - Theft-Movable Property, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a class A Misdemeanor.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.
Count 2 - Theft-Movable Property, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a class A Misdemeanor.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.
Count 3 - Criminal Damage to Property, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.01(1), a class A Misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.


Court sentenced defendant to serve THREE (3) DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for THREE (3) days served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

COUNT(S) 2 AND 3 ARE CONCURRENT TO EACH OTHER AND TO COUNT 1;  Time served disposition.  

* Restitution payable to SOCIETY INSURANCE for ONE THOUSAND EIGHT HUNDRED SIXTY-FIVE DOLLARS AND FIFTY-THREE CENTS ($1,865.53) or civil judgment with tax intercept.  Bail to be applied if applicable.  

* Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 02-08-2017 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
